		<title>02Communications in Chalton</title>
		<content> There is a public telephone kiosk and 
 a post box between the Old Post Office
 and the Red Lion.                     
                                       
 The morning post arrives between 8.15 
 and  9.00.  The postman usually has a 
 quick  cup  of  coffee  in a house in 
 Woodcroft  Lane.  There is no second  
 post delivery to the Woodcroft end of 
 Chalton.                              
                                       
 One of the wives interviewed used to  
 be the  Cookery  editress of Woman's  
 Weekly.                               
                                       
 Most of the people  interviewed said a
 phone was a necessity in a rural area.
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
